Willowvale police in the Eastern Cape arrested a 25-year-old suspect on Thursday in connection with the murder of a 27-year-old man. Police Spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha, said both the suspect and the deceased attended a traditional ceremony when a quarrel broke out in Rhaladiya Location, Chafutweni village. The suspect allegedly drew his knife and stabbed the victim in the chest, before fleeing on foot. The 25-year-old man is expected to appear in the Willowvale Magistrate s Court on Monday. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.